  </div>
</section>

<section class="sectionbody">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-7 col-md-12">
        <div class="descriphold">
          <h1 class="headingholding">People will search for your Business</h1>
          <p style="font-weight: 700;">Many people search for solutions and answers to their problems. Many people will search for your business. You have to make sure they find you. You are their solution</p>
          <p style="font-weight: 300; text-align: left;">
           We have all searched or better still we always search the internet for things we want. Most of us never go beyond the first page of the search results page. ANytime you search for on google or any other search engine, the order in which search results are displayed is based on complex algorithms. These search engines take into consideration a number of factors into account before deciding  which website to show first, second, third and subsequently. Truth is that you may not be the only person providing that service or selling that product. When customers search for terms relating to your business, it should be your aim to appear in at least the first five websites the search engines pick. This means more traffic to your website, more visitors, implying more sales or more client requests. There are certain criteria you have to meet before your website appears in the top searc results. Lets help you fulfill this criteria. Meaning more customers, more clients. Fill the form on your right and lets start optimizing your site for more sales and traffic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-12">
        <div class="ctahold">
          <h1 class="landingheader" style="font-weight: bold; text-align: center; color: white; font-size: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Kindly fill this form.</h1>

       <%= form_for(@potential) do |f| %>
  <div class="form-group">
    <div class="form-group">
    <label style="font-weight: bold; color: white;">Name</label>
    <input type="text" name="potential[name]" id="potential_name" class="form-control" placeholder="Your Name">
  </div>
    <label style="font-weight: bold; color: white;">Email</label>
    <input type="email" name="potential[email]" id="potential_email" class="form-control" placeholder="Email Address">
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label style="font-weight: bold; color: white;">Phone Number</label>
    <input type="text" name="potential[phone]" id="potential_phone" class="form-control" placeholder="Your Phone number">
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label style="font-weight: bold; color: white;">Organization's Name</label>
    <input type="text" name="potential[orgname]" id="potential_orgname" class="form-control" placeholder="Organization's Name">
  </div>
  <input type="hidden" name="potential[searcheo]" id="potential_searcheo" value="Search Engine Optimization">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label style="font-weight: bold; color: white;">Any Objectives in mind?</label>
   <textarea class="form-control" name="potential[goal]" id="potential_goal" rows="3" placeholder="Increase my sales by 45%, Get new clients every week, etc"></textarea>
  </div>
  <br>
       <p style="color: #fff; text-align: center;">Response time is usually within an hour.</p> 
        <p style="text-align: center;"><button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary websubmit btn-lg">Send Marketing Enquiry</button></p>
      </div>
       
      
      <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
